HEADWORD: Cerebralism
<hw>Cer"e*bral*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Philos.)</fld>
<def>The doctrine or theory that psychical phenomena are functions or
products of the brain only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerebralist</ent>⟦br⟧
